  "hash": "sha256:a3f7c2e1d09b4856f1a2c3d4e5f6a7b8c9d0e1f2a3b4c5d6e7f8a9b0c1d2e3f4",
  "signature": "ed25519:b1c2d3e4f5a6b7c8d9e0f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0d1e2f3a4b5c6d7e8f9a0b1c2",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "SQA plan must document version control, regression testing suite with ≥90% coverage of solver modules, and independent code review records for all hemolysis-relevant subroutines. Required level 4 per MRL 5 mandate for Class III devices.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (OpenFOAM v9) operates under a documented SQA plan that includes Git-based version control and a regression test suite covering 78% of relevant solver modules. Independent review of the hemolysis transport subroutine was conducted internally but not by a third party. Achieved level 3 because third-party code audit and full regression coverage were not completed prior to submission."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy verification via Method of Manufactured Solutions (MMS) must be demonstrated for all governing equations including the hemolysis transport scalar. Achieved convergence rates must match theoretical order within 10%. Required level 4 for MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "MMS verification was applied to the Navier-Stokes solver and demonstrated second-order spatial accuracy. However, MMS was not extended to the hemolysis power-law transport equation, which is the primary quantity of interest. This gap reduces the achieved level to 2. The team acknowledges this as a significant epistemic gap for MRL 5 compliance."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be computed using at least three systematically refined meshes with refinement ratio ≥1.3. GCI for hemolysis index must be below 5% at the finest mesh level. Required level 4 per MRL 5 protocol.",
      "rationale": "Three mesh levels (4M, 12M, 32M cells) were evaluated with a refinement ratio of approximately 1.44. GCI for the hemolysis index at the 32M mesh was 8.3%, exceeding the 5% threshold. Velocity field GCI was 3.1% at the finest level. Achieved level 3 reflects adequate mesh convergence for flow quantities but insufficient convergence for the hemolysis scalar itself."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "The experimental validation data used for this assessment were collected under controlled bench conditions using bovine blood at 37°C across five operating points (2000–3500 RPM, 3–8 L/min). While these conditions overlap with the nominal VAD operating envelope, the validation experiments did not replicate pulsatile inflow conditions representative of in-vivo VAD use, where cardiac remnant function introduces flow variability of ±15–30%. Furthermore, the blood temperature in bench testing was maintained at 37°C ± 0.5°C, whereas in-vivo conditions may exhibit localized thermal gradients near the impeller that alter blood viscosity and consequently the hemolysis exposure time integral. The test fluid lot-to-lot variability in hematocrit (range: 38–44%) was documented but not propagated into the hemolysis model as an uncertainty source. Taken together, these gaps in test condition fidelity — particularly the absence of pulsatile boundary conditions and the unquantified thermal effects — reduce the achieved level to 3. At MRL 5 for a Class III VAD, the required level of 5 demands that test conditions be essentially equivalent to COU conditions, including in-vivo hemodynamic variability, which the current validation campaign does not satisfy. The team has identified a planned follow-on pulsatile flow validation study scheduled for Q3 2026 that is expected to address the pulsatility gap, but results are not available for this submission cycle."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted hemolysis index must agree with experimental measurements within combined simulation and experimental uncertainty bounds at all 5 operating points. Systematic bias must be characterized and shown to be below 15% of the measured mean. Required level 4 for MRL 5 Class III submission.",
      "rationale": "At 4 of 5 operating points, predicted hemolysis index values fell within the combined uncertainty bounds. At the highest flow-speed combination (3500 RPM, 8 L/min), the model over-predicted hemolysis by 22%, exceeding the 15% systematic bias threshold. This single outlier, combined with the absence of pulsatile validation data, limits the achieved level to 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The primary QOI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) must be directly linked to the clinical endpoint (plasma free hemoglobin elevation) through a documented physiological model. Secondary QOIs (wall shear stress, exposure time) must be validated independently. Required level 5 for MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "The NIH is the primary QOI and is directly compared to clinical hemolysis thresholds per ASTM F1841. Wall shear stress and scalar exposure time are validated against PIV and particle tracking data respectively. The link from NIH to plasma free hemoglobin is established through the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power law, which is documented in the model description. Achieved level 4 because the physiological link model itself was not independently validated for this specific pump geometry."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must cover the full COU operating envelope including all 5 flow-speed combinations and must use patient-representative blood analogs or human blood. Geometric similarity between validation and COU device must be demonstrated. Required level 5 for MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on the FDA generic pump geometry, which is identical to the COU device. Bovine blood was used rather than human blood, introducing species-dependent RBC fragility differences. Only 3 of 5 COU operating points were covered in the validation campaign due to experimental constraints. Achieved level 3 reflects partial coverage of the operating envelope and non-human blood use."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence must be demonstrated to residual levels below 1e-6 for all equations. Floating point round-off error must be quantified for the hemolysis transport scalar. Required level 4 for MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence to 1e-5 was achieved for velocity and pressure fields. The hemolysis scalar residual was not independently monitored and no floating-point error analysis was performed. This factor was flagged as not-assessed for the structured evidence record; achieved level 1 reflects the absence of documented solver error quantification."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "A documented user qualification process must be in place, including evidence of analyst training on hemolysis CFD workflows and independent review of simulation setup by a second qualified analyst. Required level 3 for MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "No formal user qualification documentation was submitted. The primary analyst has 5 years of hemolysis CFD experience but no independent reviewer checked the simulation setup. This factor is flagged as not-assessed."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The hemolysis power-law model form must be justified through comparison with at least two alternative hemolysis models (e.g., Arora, Taskin) across the COU operating envelope. Sensitivity of predictions to model form must be quantified. Required level 4 for MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Only the Giersiepen-Wurzinger model was used. No alternative model form comparison was performed. Model form uncertainty is therefore unquantified and this factor is flagged as not-assessed at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters must have documented sources with associated uncertainty distributions. Monte Carlo propagation must cover all inputs with coefficient of variation above 5%. Required level 4 for MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed on three primary inputs (viscosity, inlet velocity, rotational speed). Power-law exponent and coefficient uncertainties from the Giersiepen-Wurzinger correlation were not included in the propagation. This omission is flagged as an epistemic gap."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental samples must be statistically sufficient (n≥5 per operating point) and sample variability must be reported. Hematocrit and RBC age distributions must be characterized. Required level 4 for MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Experimental hemolysis measurements used n=3 replicates per operating point. Hematocrit was reported as a range but RBC age distribution was not characterized. Sample size is insufficient for MRL 5 requirements and this factor is not-assessed."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Input parameters used in validation simulations must be demonstrated to be equivalent to those used in COU simulations within stated uncertainty bounds. Any differences must be justified and their impact on QOIs quantified. Required level 5 for MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "The validation simulations used bovine blood rheological properties while COU simulations use human blood properties. The impact of this substitution on hemolysis predictions was not quantified. This equivalency gap is a primary contributor to the overall Not Accepted decision."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou2-vad-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-vv40-lead-assessor",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The 13-factor credibility assessment for COU2 (VAD hemolysis prediction, MRL 5) demonstrates that 7 factors were assessed with achieved levels ranging from 2 to 4 against required levels of 3 to 5, and 6 factors were not assessed due to epistemic gaps in experimental data and model form characterization. No factor achieved its required level. The overall credibility is insufficient for a Class III VAD submission at MRL 5. The assessment team recommends a structured remediation plan addressing pulsatile validation, alternative hemolysis model comparison, and expanded experimental sample sizes before resubmission.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
